JOHANNESBURG – Wits University on Saturday said it was investigating a potential racist incident involving one of its lecturers. It is alleged he sent out an email in which he called striking workers on campus monkeys. In an apparent email sent from him, the lecturer apologised for the remark, saying the comment was not meant to be prejudicial. READ: Wits professor found guilty of sexual harassment dismissed The university said it was trying to ascertain the authenticity of the mail after receiving a formal complaint. It will then decide on the appropriate action to take against him. The lecturer allegedly works for the mechanical engineering department. eNCA